  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>Expectation of the roles and responsibilities: Minimum experience of at least 6 years in project management/Coordination roles, ideally in the landscaping, construction or A&amp;A works, <strong>sense of urgency, strong sense of mission</strong> and costing.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Company Transport Will be Provided.</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>1) Attend Site Meetings and conduct Daily Toolbox meetings with workers.</p>\n<p>2) Planning and present schedule using scheduling software and daily coordination work for multiple sites.</p>\n<p>3) Managing client's calls on Site progress and answering enquiries on Site related issues as fast as possible on all form of communication channels like whatsapp or Email.</p>\n<p>4) Logistics planning for transport of materials and equipment on site, including tracking site material usages as well as coordination with subcontractor removal works specialist.</p>\n<p>5) Administrative routine such as submission of safety related documentation prior to the start of work which consists of safe work procedures, method of statement for work and Risk Assessment.</p>\n<p>6) Risk management implementation for Site Safety compliance.</p>\n<p>7) Ensuring workers meet their monthly work completion targets on site and provide advance catch-up schedules if needed.</p>\n<p>8) Able to work in a team and provide constant feedback on ways to improve existing coordination methods.</p>\n<p>9) Added advantage for those who are able to read construction drawings (Revit, autodesk, autocad)</p>\n<p>10) To be able to lead your project coordinators on Site survey and site measurement including attending official Handover meeting for completed Sites.</p>\n<p>11) Feedback on Worker's working rate and any compliance issues to the management.</p>\n<p>12) Highlight Site issues and provide possible suggestions to solve the problems during Weekly Internal Project Meeting.</p>\n<p>13) Commend on worker's working attitude and recommend fines for those who is found liable of causing safety problems or conflicts among workers.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 6,
